cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with improving the performance of deep neural networks in classification tasks by leveraging class similarity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a modified loss function, which could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
